parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air suspension system can cause the vehicle to ride unevenly, making it difficult to control, and increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle becomes very bouncy
the suspension system defaults to the highest level
the vehicle shakes and bounces over slight imperfections in the road
the vehicle feels like it will tip over when making turns
the "AHC OFF" light keeps flashing
the vehicle sits very low and will not come up to the "N" level
the vehicle oscillates from front to back.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Variable Gear Ratio Steering (VGRS) Electronic Control Unit (ECU) Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the VGRS ECU can cause a severe alignment mismatch between the steering wheel and the front tires, making it difficult to control the vehicle, increasing the risk of loss of control, collision, and injury.
symptoms: The steering wheel is off-center by 20-120 degrees to drive in a straight line
making it difficult to keep the vehicle driving in a straight line
the VGRS indicator light is active
and the steering wheel alignment is progressively worsening over time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel evaporative system can cause excessive fuel pressure in the gas tank, leading to pressurized fuel vapors escaping from the gas cap, which is a fire risk and a safety concern.
symptoms: Fuel smell in the cabin
fuel vapors coming out of the fuel door/gas cap
audible venting of the fuel tank
gasoline boiling sound in the tank
continuous escape of gasoline vapors under pressure when the gas cap is removed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The airbag warning light staying on can indicate a malfunction in the airbag system, which can lead to failure to deploy in the event of an accident, potentially resulting in serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the dashboard remains illuminated
indicating a potential issue with the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Repair for Airbag Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of repair for the airbag recall can leave the vehicle in an unsafe condition, potentially leading to failure to deploy in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: Dealerships do not have the necessary parts to repair the airbag system
leaving the vehicle in an unsafe condition
and owners are unable to get the recall remedied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rust and corrosion on the frame can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to safety risks and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion on the front frame
particularly around the sway bar and brackets
and other areas of the frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire blowouts can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden tire blowout
loss of air pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Poor Aftermarket Installation and Electrical Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor installation of aftermarket accessories can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: DVD system malfunction
navigation system not working properly
speakers not working
radio shutting off during calls
poor AM reception
instrument panel cover damage due to oil and water splashing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor vehicle handling can increase the risk of accidents, especially in adverse weather conditions.
symptoms: Vehicle handling poorly in snowy conditions.
